## Test-Driven Development (TDD)

- Write the test before the implementation, not after
- Red → Green → Refactor cycle is the expected loop
- Tests live in a `tests/` directory at the repo root unless the project has an
  established convention already
- Test file naming: `test_<module>.py` (Python) or `<module>.test.js` (JavaScript)
- Every non-trivial function should have at least one test
- Edge cases and failure modes are first-class test citizens — not afterthoughts
- Claude Code should run the test suite after every implementation change and
  report results before declaring a task done

### Python testing
- Use `pytest` as the default test runner
- Use `pytest-cov` for coverage reporting when coverage is relevant
- Fixtures over setup/teardown methods

