## Code Style

### General
- Clarity over cleverness — write code your future self will understand at 2am
- Functions do one thing
- Name things accurately; avoid abbreviations except universally understood ones
- No magic numbers — name your constants

### Python
- Follow PEP 8
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Docstrings on public functions (Google style)
- `black` for formatting if configured; otherwise consistent 4-space indentation;
   120-char width

### JavaScript
- Prefer `const` over `let`; avoid `var`
- Arrow functions for callbacks; named functions for anything with logic
- No framework assumed globally — check project CLAUDE.md for per-project stack

