## What Claude Code Should Always Do

- Read existing code before writing new code — don't assume structure
- Run the test suite after changes; don't declare done until tests pass
- Ask before deleting or significantly restructuring existing files
- Prefer small, verifiable steps over large one-shot rewrites
- If a task touches more than ~3 files, propose a plan first and wait for approval